<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF110-374-510  </DOCNO><DOCID>10 374 510.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Information Systems  July 1990 v8 n3 p181(23).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>The UAN: a user-oriented representation for direct manipulationinterface designs. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hartson, H. Rex; Siochi, Antonio C.; Hix, Deborah.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A behavioral view of the user performing tasks to interact withthe computer is essential for user-centered interface design.andP;  Theactions used to accomplish tasks are described by User ActionNotation (UAN).andP;  UAN is a behavior representation that uses atext-based representation, making analytical evaluation ofinterfaces possible.andP;  Interfaces in UAN are specified as aquasihierarchy of asynchronous tasks.andP;  Visually onompatopeicsymbols are used in UAN, so little instruction is necessary to beable to read UAN.andP;  Tests with real-world users show UAN to be highreadable and writable because of its simplicity and naturalmnemonicity.andP;  When used to convey large complex user interfacedesigns from designers to implementers and evaluators, UAN isthorough, concise, and precise.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Human FactorsDesignSoftware EngineeringUser InterfaceLanguageTask AnalysisInterface.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   UAN description of the task 'select an icon.' (chart)UAN description of the task 'select a file icon.' (chart)UAN description of the task 'delete a file.' (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>